$ SQLPATH - spooling helpers
@ spooling helpers for SQL*Plus

`spool.sql` sets some → development/databases/Oracle/SQL-Plus settings in a way, that the → development/databases/Oracle/SQL-Plus/spool[`spool`] command writes clean files.
These files are used, for example, in → development/databases/Oracle/SQL-Plus/sqlpath/insert_statement_creator[`insert_statement_creator.sql`].

{ spool.sql

  Start spooling in a clean way:

  gh|Oracle-SQLPATH|/spool.sql||

}
{ spool_off.sql

  End spooling

  gh|Oracle-SQLPATH|/spool_off.sql||

}

sa:
  → development/databases/Oracle/SQL-Plus/sqlpath
